The pipette calibration device is an instrument used for calibrating and verifying the performance of pipettes. It measures the actual amount of liquid aspirated or dispensed by the pipette and compares it with the nominal volume indicated by the pipette, determining any deviation. Through adjustments it ensures that dispensed volumes fall within specified tolerances, guaranteeing accuracy and reliability in scientific research, medical treatment, and chemical analysis.
