What is a Pipette Calibration Device?
A pipette calibration device is a precision instrument that ensures liquid handling instruments operate within their specified accuracy limits. By delivering highly controlled displacement of liquid, these devices provide an objective benchmark that verifies whether a pipette dispenses the correct volume, thereby reducing assay variability and improving reproducibility across research, clinical, and industrial applications.
This product plays a crucial role in maintaining compliance with rigorous GMP, ISO, and regulatory requirements. Laboratories that routinely calibrate pipettes using these devices mitigate the risk of sample loss, reduce the cost of failed experiments, and uphold their reputation for high data integrity.
